In Galtuer, a town of 700 year-round inhabitants and about 3,000tourists in Tyrol Province's Paznaun Valley, the avalanchethundered though the heart of town near the village church at 4:00p.m.
European authorities explained the spate of avalanches by thealmost unparalleled amounts of snow that have fallen since thesecond week of February and the high winds that have whipped itinto drifts and made it unstable on the crust of earlier snow.
